<div class="c-accordion__content" id="content-13" aria-hidden="true" data-js-accordion-container="">

<div class="c-accordion__content-inner" itemscope="" itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">

<div itemprop="text">

<!-- START ANSWER copy HTML markup-->
<p>Yes, absolutely! Kiehl's Ultra Facial Cream works exceptionally well as a hydrating base under makeup due to: <br>

<strong>Fast Absorption:</strong> Despite being intensely hydrating, the formula is surprisingly lightweight. It sinks into the skin quickly without leaving a heavy, greasy, or sticky residue that could cause foundation to slide off.
<br>
<strong>Creates a Smooth Canvas:</strong> It contains Squalane (a highly refined moisturizing oil derived from olives) and Glacial Glycoprotein. These ingredients work together to deeply hydrate and plump the skin. When your skin is properly moisturized, makeup glides on smoothly rather than clinging to dry patches, settling into fine lines, or looking cakey.
<br>
<strong>Prevents Flaking:</strong> By strengthening the skin's moisture barrier, it ensures your skin stays hydrated throughout the day, preventing your foundation from cracking or looking patchy after a few hours of wear.  </p>
<!-- END ANSWER copy HTML markup-->

